<DOCNO> LA041494-0072 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 032010 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
April 14, 1994, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
South Bay; Part J; Page 8 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
157 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: REGION; EXTENDED POST OFFICE HOURS FOR TAX-FILERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON GARCIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Expecting the annual onslaught of last-minute tax filers, several area post 
offices will remain open until midnight Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the extended hours, most locations will have postal workers 
stationed curbside starting mid-afternoon to collect stamped returns, said 
David Mazer, a postal service spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 Four area post offices will have extended hours: 
</P>
<P>
 * Marina del Rey, Processing and Distribution Center, 13031 Jefferson Blvd. No 
window service, but stamps available until midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 * Long Beach, Main Post Office, 300 Long Beach Blvd. No window service after 5 
p.m., but special tax collections until midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 * Long Beach, Processing and Distribution Center, 2300 Redondo Ave. No window 
service after 5 p.m., but special tax collections until midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 * Los Angeles, Airport Area, Worldway Air Mail Center, 5800 W. Century Blvd. 
Window and collection service 24 hours; IRS representatives on site. JON GARCIA 
</P>
