</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A newborn girl was found dead in a trash can in Alondra Park near the city of 
Lawndale on Monday night by a man searching for aluminum cans. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified infant, who investigators believe had been born only a few 
hours before she was found, was wrapped in a size 18 or 20 long-sleeved woman's 
shirt and stuffed into a white plastic garbage bag before being put in the park 
trash can.Her umbilical cord was still attached. Sheriff's Deputy Rich Erickson 
said the 8-pound infant showed no obvious signs of trauma, but the cause of 
death has not been determined.  
</P>
<P>
 Erickson said the baby was found about 7:30 p.m. Monday in the northeast 
corner of the park near Manhattan Beach Boulevard. The shirt she was wrapped in 
was white with rust-colored stripes with "Venezia" printed on the label. Anyone 
with information about the infant is asked to call the sheriff's homicide 
bureau at (213) 890-5500. 
