<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; WOMAN HURT IN POLICE CAR ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Simi Valley police car broadsided another car Wednesday morning, critically 
injuring the other driver outside a Metrolink Station parking lot on Los 
Angeles Avenue, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the police car, Officer Rick Rinehart, a 12-year veteran, was 
not hurt, police said.But Peggy Sphar, 45, of Simi Valley apparently was not 
wearing her seat belt and was thrown from her car and suffered head injuries, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sphar, who works as a nurse at Simi Valley Hospital, was taken to the hospital 
shortly before 8 a.m. and underwent surgery, hospital spokeswoman JoLynn de la 
Torre said. Sphar was in critical condition Wednesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley Police Sgt. Mike King said detectives are still investigating the 
accident. Both Sphar's station wagon and the patrol car received moderate 
damage, King said. Rinehart was on routine patrol at the time and was not 
responding to any calls at the time of the accident, King said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
