<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY DIES AFTER SHOOTING ON SCHOOL PLAYGROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 11-year-old boy died Wednesday, a day after being shot in the head by a 
classmate on a crowded elementary school playground, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A 10-year-old boy upset over an argument the previous day at the Margaret 
Leary Elementary School fired a pistol three times Tuesday, police said. Jeremy 
Bullock, who was standing next to the intended target and about 10 feet from 
the shooter, died at St. James Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Teachers reportedly did not see the shooting, but one confiscated the gun 
after hearing shots fired. 
</P>
</TEXT>
