<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; SENIOR CENTER PLANS HEALTH SCREENINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A nonprofit center for senior citizens will have a health fair this weekend 
that is designed to encourage older people to take advantage of regular, 
preventive medical checks. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want this to be a comfortable environment for them," said Laurell 
Detweiler, program coordinator for the Oasis Senior Center."We want (seniors) 
to become more aware of their health." 
</P>
<P>
 The Health Fair Expo will provide participants with free screenings for blood 
pressure, dermatology, lungs, hearing and vision. Free tetanus shots will also 
be offered. 
</P>
<P>
 For $25, seniors can receive a blood test that checks 28 different 
chemistries, including cholesterol, sugar and sodium levels. Prostate cancer 
screenings for men will be offered for $50. 
</P>
<P>
 Detweiler stressed that the medical workers at the fair will not diagnose 
conditions based on screenings. But they will suggest that seniors get medical 
attention if tests reveal any abnormalities. 
</P>
<P>
 "If a test is out of a normal range, we will suggest they get it checked," 
Detweiler said. "If they have a blemish on their skin, we will tell them they 
need to get it checked." 
</P>
<P>
 The fair will take place Saturday from 8 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the Oasis Senior 
Center at 5th and Narcissus avenues in Corona del Mar. The center is a 
nonprofit group.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 644-3244. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
