<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 3 AUTHORS TO SPEAK AT REFORMA FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county chapter of Reforma, a national association that promotes library 
services for those who speak Spanish, will hold its second annual scholarship 
fund-raiser Saturday at the Fullerton Public Library. 
</P>
<P>
 Three Latino authors will talk about their profession.Admission is $10 for the 
general public and $5 for students. Proceeds will go toward providing 
scholarships for graduate students pursuing a master's degree in library and 
information science. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruben Martinez, a host of public television's "Life and Times" and author of 
"The Other Side"; Marisela Norte, a free-lance writer and poet whose work is 
featured on the cassette tapes "Norte/Word" and "Black and Tan Club," and Frank 
Ortega, co-author of "5 Orange County Poets," will sign books and tapes and 
read from their work. 
</P>
<P>
 The event begins at 7 p.m. at the library, 353 W. Commonwealth Ave.MIMI KO 
</P>
