<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; GREENE PUT ON DISABLED LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pitcher Tommy Greene of the Philadelphia Phillies was put on the 15-day 
disabled list because of tendinitis in his right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Rev. Jesse Jackson has offered to help organize an ethic minority baseball 
ownership group to purchase the Oakland Athletics and keep the team in Oakland. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A 15-year-old girl in Victoria, Tex., has dropped a lawsuit in which she 
accused former Atlanta Brave outfielder Ron Gant and his cousin of conspiring 
to have sex with her. 
</P>
