<P>
FREEWAY LEAGUE; SUNNY HILLS UPSETS NO. 3 FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Josh Hochgesang's run-scoring double in the fourth inning gave Sunny Hills a 
5-4 victory over third-ranked Fullerton in a Freeway League baseball game 
Wednesday at Sunny Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Guzman had a three-run double in a four-run first inning for the Lancers 
(8-8-1, 4-2).Fullerton fell to 13-3, 5-1. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first loss of the season for Fullerton pitcher Ryan Golisano (7-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park 5, Sonora 0 -- Mike Davis (2-0) gave up four hits in recording his 
second consecutive shutout for Buena Park (8-6, 4-2). Greg Cabral hit his 
fourth home run of the season in the fifth inning and Johnny Cabral added three 
hits and one RBI for Buena Park. 
</P>
