<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR BEATS UNIVERSITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seniors Jed Weinstein and Paul Fruchbom, pairing up for the first time since 
they were freshmen, won three doubles sets to lead Corona del Mar to an 11-10 
victory over visiting University in a Sea View League boys' tennis match 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea Kings, 15 2/3-5 2/3 losers to University the first time the teams met, 
won three singles and six doubles sets to pull out the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Weinstein and Fruchbom won 6-1, 7-5, 6-2. Roberto Intriago, who normally is 
paired with Fruchbom, joined Tyler Stonebreaker for a pair of victories, 7-5, 
6-2, and Doug Smith and Mike Feyka won, 6-4, for Corona del Mar (10-2, 7-1), 
which moved into a tie for first with University (9-2, 7-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Because doubles victories are worth 1 1/3, Corona del Mar Coach Tim Mang 
shuffled his lineup and it worked. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was hoping (University coach) Josh (Davis) would move Jason Meyers to 
doubles, giving our singles a chance," Mang said. 
</P>
<P>
 Meyers, the Trojans' top player, ended up losing two doubles sets. 
</P>
<P>
 Three sets went to 7-5 with Corona del Mar winning all three on service breaks 
in the final game. MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
