<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES / ANNE MICHAUD: HONORS TO CHIEF CHEF AT ANTOINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jean Pierre Lemanissier, chef of Restaurant Antoine in Newport Beach, was 
named "Chef of the Year" on Sunday by the Southern California Restaurant 
Writers Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Lemanissier, a native of Dunkerque, France, served his apprenticeship with 
Paul Bocuse in Bocuse's Lyon, France, restaurant, Collonges-au-Mont-d'Or. He 
went on to become chef de partie for the restaurant of London's Connaught Hotel 
and sous chef for Los Angeles' L'Ermitage. He served as chef de cuisine at Ma 
Maison and at the restaurant in the Four Seasons Hotel in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Past winners include Pascal Olhats of Pascal in Newport Beach and Alan Greeley 
of the Golden Truffle in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 And speaking of Antoine, guests are invited to bring their Bordeaux wines for 
a bring-your-own-bottle menu tonight and Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinner, which is $65 per person plus tax and tip, includes a mixed Chino Farm 
vegetable salad, sauteed monkfish with fennel, goat cheese with green olive 
sauce, squab with four-leaf salad and braised pork loin in coconut milk. For 
dessert, the chef plans to make his grandmother's recipe for light chocolate 
mousse. 
</P>
<P>
 Corkage fees are waived for the event. Dinner hours are 6 to 10 p.m. on 
Thursdays and 6 to 10:30 p.m. on Fridays. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Hotel Meridien, 4500 MacArthur Blvd., Newport Beach. (714) 476-2001, 
ext. 2158. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Raffaello Ristorante will offer a four-course dinner and wine-tasting Tuesday 
evening at 7:30. Cocktails begin at 7. 
</P>
<P>
 The price is $47, not including tax or tip. On the menu is puffed pastry 
filled with porcini mushrooms, bow-shaped pasta sauteed with rock shrimp and 
scallops, roasted veal chop and chocolate souffle. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations are recommended. 
</P>
<P>
 1998 N. Tustin Ave., Orange. (714) 283-8230. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Emporio Armani Express has begun an "aperitivo," or happy hour, from 4 to 6:30 
p.m., Monday through Friday. The South Coast Plaza restaurant will serve free 
appetizers during those hours. Also, on Fridays, the restaurant plans to 
present informal modeling of clothes from Emporio Armani. 
</P>
<P>
 3333 Bristol St., Costa Mesa. (714) 754-0300. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Overture Company of Opera Pacific will entertain diners at Gustaf Anders 
from 6:30 to 8:30 p.m. on Wednesday with a selection of love songs, popular 
duets and arias. Doors open at 5:30. 
</P>
<P>
 1651 Sunflower Ave., South Coast Plaza Village, Santa Ana. (714) 668-1737. 
</P>
<P>
 Information for the Newsbites column can be faxed to (714) 966-5663 or mailed 
to Newsbites/OC Live!, The Times Orange County, 1375 Sunflower Ave., CA 92626. 
Or call (714) 966-7898.  
</P>
