<HEADLINE>
<P>
PELE SAYS MARADONA IS WASHED UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three-time World Cup winner Pele said Wednesday that Argentina's Diego 
Maradona is so far past his best he should not even play in this summer's World 
Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 Pele, who helped Brazil win the World Cup in 1958, 1962 and 1970, said 
Maradona is only a shadow of the player who led Argentina to the World Cup 
title in 1986 and to second-place in Italy four years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "I tried to talk to his friends and his manager two years ago and advise him 
to stop playing because he's not at his best," Pele said. "Now, he keeps 
trying. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think he's going to be in the best condition to play in this World 
Cup like he played before. I don't think that he's mentally and psychologically 
prepared for the World Cup. I feel sorry, because he's a great player." 
</P>
