<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPLASH SELECT FULLERTON RESIDENT GYAU IN THE CISL DRAFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Splash, Anaheim's new entry in the Continental Indoor Soccer League, 
selected Fullerton resident Phillip Gyau with its first pick in Wednesday's 
league draft in Washington, D.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Gyau, a 6-foot-1, 170-pound forward, was most valuable player of the American 
Professional Soccer League in 1990 but has no indoor pro experience. The Splash 
selected him 38th overall. 
</P>
<P>
 The Splash used their other pick, in the 10th round, for defender Denis 
Hamlett, a member of the Harrisburg Heat of the indoor National Professional 
Soccer League. 
</P>
<P>
 With three other picks, the Splash protected three members of the old L.A. 
United, which played in the CISL last year and was sold to the group that 
created the Splash. The players are former UCLA midfielder Sam George, forward 
Raffaele Ruotolo -- the United's leading scorer last season with 24 goals in 19 
games -- and forward Bobby Reyes. 
</P>
<P>
 The first pick overall by the Las Vegas Dust was Branko Segota, all-time 
leading scorer for the San Diego Sockers of the old Major Soccer League. 
</P>
<P>
 The Splash begins play June 10 at The Pond of Anaheim. 
</P>
