<HEADLINE>
<P>
A RENAISSANCE AFFAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's rowdy and a tad raunchy, daring and delightful -- an outdoor fair like no 
other in this century. The annual Renaissance Pleasure Faire returns weekends 
and Memorial Day beginning Saturday, through June 5, at the field adjacent to 
Blockbuster Pavilion, in Glen Helen Regional Park in Devore (off I-15 in San 
Bernardino). 
</P>
<P>
 Armored knights will demonstrate their riding and jousting skills and Her 
Majesty's soldiers will go to battle against renegade Scots. Crafts, music and 
dancing and strolling performers add to the period ambience. 
</P>
<P>
 The Elizabethan village atmosphere is full of activities for children, 
including the Dragon Maze, a five-person swing, merry-go-round and a free 
crafts area, called Mistress Miranda's Traditional School. 
</P>
<P>
 Foods include corn on the cob, turkey legs, imported sausages, shepherd's pie 
and sweets. Hours are 9 a.m.-6 p.m. Admission is $16.50 ($14.50 in advance); 
students, seniors and military, $13.50; children 5-11, $7.50. Parking is $5. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (800) 523-2473. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
