<P>
 Daimler-Benz Reports Worst Performance Since WWII: Germany's largest 
industrial group reported a loss of $1.08 billion for 1993, compared to a 
$791-million profit in 1992.The loss, which is according to U.S. accounting 
rules that the company adopted when it was listed on the New York Stock 
Exchange last year, is the group's worst performance since World War II. The 
Mercedes-Benz luxury car subsidiary posted an operating loss of $742.2 million, 
contrasted with a $1.34-billion profit in 1992. Daimler-Benz Chairman Edzard 
Reuter said the company is expected to have an operating profit this year. He 
said the group made an operating profit in the first quarter of 1994 and sales 
rose 15%. 
</P>
