<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: ANAHEIM FIRM PLANS WIRELESS LINE OF PRODUCTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home Theater Products International, which makes and sells consumer electronic 
products, said Wednesday it will introduce a line of wireless audio, video and 
multimedia products during the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which specializes in home surround-sound systems, said it will be 
the first to offer a complete home theater system using infrared and 900 MHz 
technology in its components and not as accessories.Infrared technology, now 
used in fiber optic data communication and TV remote controls, is more reliable 
than conventional technology, the company said, and use of radio frequency 
bands in the 900 MHz range can result in more accurate transmissions with less 
interference. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, based in Anaheim, reported earnings of $700,000 on sales of $8.1 
million for its latest quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
