<P>
 Burlington Air Express: IBM de Mexico, the Mexican affiliate of the U.S. 
computer giant, has awarded a two-year contract worth at least $3.2 million to 
Burlington Air Express in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The contract calls for Burlington to ship computers and peripheral equipment 
from IBM's plant in Guadalajara, Mexico, to distributors in Chile, Venezuela, 
Peru, Uruguay, Bolivia, Paraguay and Colombia. 
</P>
<P>
 Burlington, a subsidiary of the Pittston Co. of Stamford, Conn., was awarded a 
contract that has an option for another year, which would raise its value by 
another $1.6 million, according to the company. 
